post_text:
For those with kids in Kindergarten and 1st grade:

Dear Parents/Guardians of Meadowbrook School Kindergarten and First Grade Students:

Good afternoon. This is Mr. McCue, Superintendent of Schools, with a special emergency message for Meadowbrook School parents and guardians Grades Kindergarten and First only.

Tomorrow, Tuesday, March 24th, parents or guardians can pick-up learning packets and materials for students in grades Kindergarten and First beginning at 7:30 am to 2:30 pm. These educational materials will support student learning at home through Spring Break. These packets can be picked up at the front of Meadowbrook School in a Grab and Go manner. Please make every effort to pick-up these materials tomorrow from 7:30 am to 2:30 pm.

Please be safe and be healthy. Thank you for your support and cooperation.

Scott T. McCue

Superintendent of Schools

shared_text:
Eatontown Schools PTA Gift Auction
March 12 at 4:15 PM ·

In light of the guidance and precautionary measures set forth by the State of New Jersey, the Eatontown Schools PTA Gift Auction will be postponed. The safety and well-being of our residents and students are our first priority. The new date for this event is Friday, June 26 at Branches Catering - an end of year auction! If you still plan on attending the event, you don't need to do anything further. More detailed communication and reminders will be sent out as we get closer to the new date. If you are no longer able to attend and cannot find a replacement for your seat, please reach out here or contact the PTA at your earliest convenience. Thank you for your understanding. On behalf of the PTA and the entire school district, we wish you and your family well.

post_text:
Tonight was my last PTA meeting as President! When we started this school year as a new district-wide PTA, I had lots of hopes and some worries! Now, at the end of the year, I feel that the pros most certainly outweighed the cons and I’m so glad that I was able to bring leadership to our new organization and I’m so grateful that I got to work with so many great people who stepped up to make this year as successful as it was! I hope the Eatontown Schools PTA continues to grow for many years to come!

Thanks!
Carrie Krueger

Leadership is definitely a big deal in the PTA!!! Did you know that a PTA can not run without a President and Treasurer? Our other officer positions are equally as important, too!

After our PTA meeting tonight, we are still in need of a Treasurer and Secretary for our PTA for next school year! If you’re interested in either of these positions, please email the Nominating Committee at eatontownschoolspta@gmail.com.
